author: Nathaniel Cline, cleveland.com
title: Eastlake North's Destiny Leo wins Game Balls basketball contest from Feb. 20, 2017
text:
More News | More Photos | More Videos Destiny Leo from the Eastlake North girls basketball team. (Photo courtesy of Eastlake North Athletics) 
CLEVELAND, Ohio â€” Eastlake North's Destiny Leo won the Game Balls basketball contest for the week of Feb. 20, 2017. 
The freshman guard led the Rangers to road wins at Ravenna and Perry. Leo finished with 49 points, 15 rebounds, nine assists, six blocks and three steals while connecting on seven 3-pointers in both games. 
She won with 5,460 votes . Bedford's Ziona Williams was second with 3,831 votes . 
The full results are below. 
Destiny Leo, Eastlake North 5,460 votes 
Ziona Williams, Bedford 3,831 votes 
Cate Schmiedl, Fairview 457 votes 
Lexi Wood, Columbia 307 votes 
Payton Pooler, St. Vincent-St. Mary 242 votes 
Total Votes: 10,297 
About Leo: Started all 23 games as a freshman and averages 13.5 ppg, 5.7 rebounds, 2.4 assists, 1.7 blocks, 1.6 steals and is shooting 30 percent from three point (38/126) and 79 percent from the free throw line (62/78). She is the team leader in 3-pointers and blocks and is second on the team in points and assists. She is averaging 18 points per game over our last 5 games (wins over Kenston, Perry, Ravenna, Brush and a loss to Mayfield).
